column12: MODIFIED ROTOR COMPONENT AND METHOD FOR MODIFYING WEAR CHARACTERISTIC OF ROTOR COMPONENT IN TURBINE SYSTEM
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a modified rotor component and a method for modifying a wear characteristic of a rotor component in a turbine system.SOLUTION: A method for modifying a wear characteristic of a rotor component in a turbine system and a modified rotor component for a turbine system are disclosed. The method includes implanting ions of one of a Group 6 element, a Group 13 element, or a metalloid element through an exterior surface of a rotor component. The rotor component is one of a rotor wheel or a distance wheel.
column15: DAVID VINCENT BUCCI;;STEVEN GERRARD POPE;;PAROLINI JASON ROBERT

column12: THREE-DIMENSIONAL SILICON-BASED COMB PROBE WITH OPTIMIZED BIOCOMPATIBLE DIMENSIONS FOR NEURAL SENSING & STIMULATION
column13: A structure for monitoring and stimulation includes an external power supply unit. The structure also includes an internal hub communicatively coupled to the external power supply unit. The structure further includes a plurality of sensor modules communicatively coupled to the internal hub by a plurality of flexible interconnects. The plurality of sensor modules include three-dimensional (3D) comb sensor devices.
